This is my second project using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) in Python.

I've recreated the classic Snake Game using multiple classes and modules to strengthen my understanding of OOP concepts through practical application.

---

## ğŸš€ Features

- Snake movement controlled via arrow keys
- Random food generation
- Snake grows upon eating food
- Scoreboard updates in real-time
- Collision detection:
  - Snake hits wall = Game Over
  - Snake collides with itself = Game Over
- Game boundary rendering with Turtle graphics

---

## ğŸ§  OOP Concepts Practiced

- Class and object creation
- Encapsulation (each module has a separate responsibility)
- Inheritance (used in `Scoreboard` class)
- Modular design and code organization

